text: Greene County is a county in Virginia in the eastern United States. As of the 2020 census, the population was 20,552. The county seat is Stanardsville. Greene County was founded in 1838 from Orange County. The county is named for American Revolutionary War hero Nathanael Greene. == References == Category:1830s establishments in Virginia Category:1838 establishments in the United States Category:Virginia counties
title: Greene County, Virginia
